/* ============================================================================
   Jewish History Explorer — Jewish population by country, over time
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   ⚠️ ILLUSTRATIVE SEED. A hand-authored spine of pivotal countries — enough to
   define the schema and seed the map. The full dataset is being assembled by
   research (see README → Phase B):
       1880–2025  ← Sergio DellaPergola / American Jewish Year Book, Pew, JVL
       pre-1880   ← historical scholarship — necessarily APPROXIMATE estimates

   Schema — keyed by ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 (matches countries.geojson ISO_A2):
       n : display name
       s : { <sliceId> : { pop, share? }, ... }
           sliceId ∈ TAXO.TIME_SLICES ids ('-1800' … '2025'; negative = BCE)
           pop   = estimated number of Jews resident (absolute)
           share = % of the country's population that is Jewish (optional; the
                   "density" metric. Omitted where unknown — only IL is ever a
                   majority; the Pale provinces were the densest diaspora.)
       note : (optional) short caveat shown in the detail card.

   Omit a slice when genuinely unknown — the renderer interpolates from the
   nearest known anchors, and shows "no data" before a territory's first entry.

   ⚠️ MODERN BORDERS AT EVERY ERA are a visualization device. The Russian Empire's
   ~5M Jews (1880) are split here across today's RU / UA / BY / LT / MD / PL.
   "Israel" carries the Land of Israel / Judea through antiquity.
   ========================================================================== */
